Finding Aids    Rare Books    Maps & GIS    Digital Images    Using Special Collections & University Archives    Special Collections Research Guides       Eyebrow menu    Contact Us    My Accounts    Give to the Library    COVID-19    UIC menu    UIC.edu    Campus Map    UIC Today     Toggle Search                  Help     Search   Search   Expand search box              Help Search Results           Search for articles, databases and journals    You can search for articles in databases and journals. Databases search many journals in a discipline or subject.    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana             Order documents (alumni and non-UIC affiliates)    If you are not a UIC student, faculty or staff member, you can order documents from the UIC Library collection for a fee. UIC students, faculty and staff can order articles for no cost through interlibrary loan.    Richard J. Daley Library  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana             Visit Special Collections and University Archives    Two reading rooms are dedicated to researchers using our collections. View Special Collections and University Archives hours at Daley Library or Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago .    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago             Access Clinical Key    ClinicalKey is a peer-reviewed, evidence-based point-of-care clinical information service for physicians and healthcare professionals. It provides electronic books, medical journals, clinical resources, practice guidelines and content from PubMed/MEDLINE. ClinicalKey replaces the content formerly offered through MD Consult.    Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana             Access UpToDate    UpToDate is an online, peer-reviewed clinical decision support tool with topic reviews covering symptoms, tests and diagnosis, and treatment options for over 8,500 conditions. Off-campus users do not need to log in to their account to access the database.    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana             Distance education user services    The Library offers many services to distance education users and online students who connect to UIC remotely.    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana             Learn about the history of UIC    Special Collections and University Archives has many resources to help researchers learn about the history of UIC. Visit our Research UIC history guide or Ask a Librarian for more information.    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana             Use an archival finding aid    A “finding aid” describes the contents of an archival collection. It is the first thing to look at before handling a collection at Special Collections and University Archives.    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago             Donate papers or transfer records to Special Collections and University Archives    Call us at (312) 996-2742 (Daley Special Collections), (312) 996-8977 (Health Sciences-Chicago Special Collections) or Ask a Librarian to see if the UIC Special Collections and University Archives is the right home for your papers.    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana             Find an archival collection    UIC Special Collections and University Archives holds a variety of materials that are available to researchers and we offer several resources to aid you in your search.    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago             Recommend an item for the library to purchase    Is there a book, DVD or other item you think UIC should own? Provide as much information on the item as you can and give your personal contact information if you want to be the first in line to borrow it.  NOTE: Requests will be held until July 2020. The library cannot purchase materials until July because all I-Share libraries are migrating to a new library system. We regret the inconvenience.    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana             Get textbooks    You can find textbooks for some courses in the Library, but you may have to buy or rent a required edition for your class. Search for textbooks in the Library Catalog.    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana             Search for films, videos and sound recordings    Search for media from several Illinois libraries (not just UIC) with the home page search, or browse options for streaming film, videos and sound recordings.    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana             Find course reserves (students)    You can find course reserves by searching the UIC Library Catalog .    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana             Search for newspapers and magazines    The Library subscribes to online versions of many newspapers and magazines. Daley Library and the Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford also offer certain periodicals in print.    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana             Renew or find out when items are due    The best way to find out when an item is due is to check your library account and your interlibrary loan account . Most books may be renewed using your library account. You cannot renew videos.  If you have trouble logging in, set up your Library account .    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana             Print (Peoria campus)    Printing is available to UIC students and residents with established print accounts, in the Library Learning Lab and the Public area of the Library. *Printing is not available to visitors.    Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria             Print (Rockford campus)    Printing is available to UIC students, faculty, residents and staff from computers in the library and the Information Commons.    Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford             Reserve the Learning Lab in Peoria    Faculty, staff and residents can reserve the Library Learning Lab for group learning, educational sessions, classroom instruction and testing.    Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria             Print, scan and copy    Printing, scanning and copying are available at all library locations.  printers prin